The paper deals with sensor fusion for perception in robotics applications, specifically for autonomous vehicle navigation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also focuses on combining camera and lidar sensors, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of probabilistic methods and modelling uncertainty suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of ego-motion estimation, which is a key issue in control systems, suggesting that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
